caption: Cool drinks, great ambiance, excellent staff.
Great drinks, made with liquor distilled on premise! Also great food! (now with sushi)
CH DISTILLERY IS THE BEST PLACE IN CHICAGO, BY FAR. YOU WILL NOT REGRET COMING HERE!
Not safe. The owner hosted a super spreader event there tonight, and some maskless woman from his party threatened me.

A friend and I visited the Christmas pop up yesterday. The cocktail menu is fantastic with about 8+ unique holiday themed cocktail to choose from, all using their own liquors. Our waitress was great and had good recommendations. You can sit inside close to the big window they have open for air flow, so it’s a much warmer option than many restaurants that only do tents. They have heaters outside the big window to warm it up. Still dress appropriately but we were not cold. We will be back soon!
Great, friendly service!

My Wife and I enjoyed our visit to CH Distillery and Cocktail Bar.  The drinks/bartenders were very good.  Once in the restaurant, the food was delicious.  Service was a tad slow, but at the same time, it was more like they were trying not to rush us.  Everyone was nice and the food was quality.

The female manager who was our server, forgot her name, gave us the best service I have received in awhile. I went for my surprise birthday dinner. They really know how to take care of their clientele. I would definitely recommend going and I will for sure be going back!
The entire staff are amazing people to kick it with, completely understanding and down to earth. The atmosphere, the food, the drinks, everything is *Chef's Kiss*
never had the food. they get five stars for the cocktails alone. also their booze is top notch. take home a bottle or two.

CH Distillery and Cocktail Bar: Pharmacy This place is simply AMAZING, speak-easy type of vibe. You'll find this hidden gem in the outskirts of Chinatown, tucked away in a corner. The Mixologists in pharmacist-style garb (super cute idea I might add) whip up some amazing drinks. Decor is simply beautiful, I will definitely come back.

This slick tasting room has a cool, naturalistic look with exposed concrete posts and knotty wood beams across the ceiling. Slip into a seat at the bar and watch the silver tanks behind the big glass window distilling the organic vodka and gin that go into your creative cocktail.
A nice place with very good cocktails and surprisingly good food for a distillery bar. I would recommend this place. You can get your bottles to go and not at all expensive bottles. Service is good.
Really innovative cocktails, tried a few and they were all good. Street parking would be free if you go after 10pm!

Bought 2 packs of anti-hero with my 2 revolution malort purchase. When I showed up they were out of (arguably the most popular and widely available) revolution beer and I was told I’d receive a refund. Here we are, 18 days later, and not only have I not received a refund but my messages have been ignored. Don’t expect any sort of customer service or care. This is the last time I’ll be purchasing from this company.
When visiting IL, I knew I had to drop by a tiki bar which are all the rage right now. I've seen numerous friends check-in here so I made it my target for my Sunday night.

I've been to CH before and saw they had drinks kits available during these crazy times, so I decided to pick a couple up. The drinks are delicious! I got the sex on the couch and rosemary's baby. Ordering and pick up was a breeze and everything was neatly packed in a bag (they even included the tiny umbrellas!). The instructions were super simple and easy to follow. I would definitely pick up another drink kit in the future! Thanks for helping to keep us in high spirits!
Drinks are well made and good but not sure how I feel about the offspring of a night club and distillery
nice quiet spot for drinks. they have games if you're inclined.
Lovely atmosphere. Food smells amazing.
Love this place! I went to visit a friend that works there and the ambiance was so welcoming and warm. The bar is fun and it is a very fun escape from the busy city, especially if you are a tourist.
Be careful while paying by card. These people add random tips to the total without letting you know.
Pretty good stuff. Im a vodka dude and this is a vodka bar. No complaints here.
Great cocktails paired with friendly bartenders that know their way around the city. And their illuminated bar...WOW!
Wonderful place, great service, fantastic drinks.
They sell Malört and Malört merchandise here! Also crafty cocktails and some small bites.

I'm not sure how our holiday party compares to regular venue, but a good place if you like hard drinks. I rarely do, but enjoyed "Old Fashioned." Hard working and friendly staff. Not a good spot for intimate conversation. They no longer brew there, but equipment looks nice. Close to Ogilvie Station if you are over the limit. Be safe.
Bland

Love CH! This is my favorite bar in the city! We’ve been going for years and have loved to see how the place has grown and developed. I highly recommend the tour they do as well as their comedy night! The food is great and I’m always impressed with the menus they offer, especially considering their kitchen space. Their beverage menu is always on point!

After my second time here, I can truly say I really love CH Distillery and Cocktail Bar! I did not love it the first time but still thought the food was pretty good.  The food is delicious and skillfully prepared. Even though this is not my preferred cuisine, I still enjoyed most of the dishes I've tried.  Make sure to utilize their sommelier who helped picked a great wine pair to our main dish. I especially loved how the sommelier did not go into any fancy explanation of the wine and just pick one he thought would go great with the pork. No bullsh*t! I'm here to enjoy myself and do not wanna hear a long explanation that I will probably forget later. Haha  We tried cocktails the first dinner and wine the second dinner and I much preferred the wine.  As for the food:  Cured meat: awesome but you can't really go wrong with cured meats!  Veal tartare: wonderful! We had to get two orders!  Chicken liver pate: Omg! Heavenly. I wanted to lick the plate.  Charred corn with uni: i liked the flavor but wish there were more uni. I barely saw any.  Mussels and clams: great flavor. Slightly spicy which I liked. Only compliant is the clams and mussels are too tiny!  Bone marrow: this is suppose to one of the favorite dishes but I did not enjoy it because it was extremely oily. I felt like I was drinking oil. The bone marrow is served with pasta which made the dish even more heavy. Flavor was also very bland.  Gizzard: not my favorite. I love gizzard for it's crunchy texture but this gizzard is cook down to a soft texture. Not the best.  Uni with lobster risotto: heavy. Flavor is not great. Again not my favorite  Cavatelli alla norcina: pretty good! Great flavor and I loved the chewiness to the pasta. The portion size is small so don't worry about get too full with the pasta.  Tomahawk pork chop: Omg! So juicy and tasty! Love the grape sauce over pork chop. Must try!  Donut: I think I was way to stuffed by the time I got here. I was physically unable to enjoy this dish.  Valet Parking is $7.50. Service was good. Ambiance was a little loud but we were still able to have a conversation. Cost is on the pricey side: about $100 per person if you order liberally.
Cocktail was awesome. Relaxed friendly bar. I would definitely go back.
A fancy place that serves up good ole malort
Always an excellent cocktail spot
Nice and fancy they sell bottles but don't let you drink them there
Darell and the chicks at the host stand deserve awards for kindness. Thank you from the frazzled chick with the bike.
Bourbon was delicious but 3$ per ice cube was not.
They bought Malort. What else do you need to know?
Very fun drink selection.
Buffalo cauliflower bites were great. One in a melon drink is delicious 👌 staff is very friendly and quick with drinks.
I love this place I'm a big g fun of distillery places in the world!
Always great to have a local Distillery close by, especially downtown, servers are knowledgeable, cocktails are fairly good, too.
Delicious and creative cocktails!
Excellent service and beautiful cocktails
The waitress and hostess were very friendly but both drinks that we ordered had way too much lemon in them and tasted super citrusy and sour
Best cocktails!

Great food and drink!
Great cocktails, friendly service. Love the video display in the bathroom, so hilarious.
Hidden gem. Great location. Cool bar. Innovative drink menu.
We came here for “Cocktails and Humor” night! The comedians were on point and did not disappoint! We were not fans of the distillery options.

Love this place. Great bar staff and the CH Peppercorn Vodka is awesome. Small kitchen turns out a nice burger. - it's a short walk from Hampton Inn that doesn't have a bar. I've been in theee times for a nightcap and will be back in two years. - thanks CH. Good luck to you.
Industrial-chic lounge features cocktails sourced from on-site stills & snazzy New American bites.

Interior very cozy with an impressive distillery setup backdrop. The cocktail glasses must have shrunk in the wash. Otherwise quite a nice spot. I would have loved to hear more about the copper distillery system.
Best bar in town! Now featuring Malort!! Great service and great drinks!
Super cocktails and great vibe. Great place to start the evening in Chicago

Drinks are good but expensive. I really hate the bar itself. It's illuminated and extremely bright while the rest of the place is pretty dark. It hurts my eyes. Maybe give it a try but don't sit at the bar.

(Translated by Google) Good option to meet, take a couple of cocktails made with their own liquors and be in a place that does not overwhelm. Regular food, good service ... But something is missing. Absolutely phenomenal cocktail bar. Didn't think there were too many places up here where you could get a great cocktail. Reminds me of violet hour down in wicker!!
Unique and interesting cocktails.  Tour was worth taking.  Small plate food was surprisingly good.  Smaller than it looks.
Great cocktails. Smart food. Pay for something you'll like.
One of my favorite places for drinks.  Especially happy hour.
Underrated, unpretentious spot with great drinks and solid food
Good cocktails and friendly bartenders. Plus, they bought the gross Chicago staple malort
New owners of Malort. This Chicago distillery has great cocktails, games and even a private event space. Check out their tour schedule online, but stop in for drinks either way.
Really good food and drinks! I thought this was a nice idea to separate themselves from other places in the area with a themed drink menu!
Enjoyed the coffee liqueur very much and purchased a bottle to take home.
Never have a walked into a bar and have the host tell my wife and I that it would be 35 minutes to get a drink!    Turned and walked out.
Excellent service, delicious and unique drinks. You won't be disappointed. And you will likely leave with a bottle of their custom spirits to take home

I've been here for several events over the past few years. It's a cool space that is never too crowded. And the staff is always super chill. It's a great spot for after street festivals like Taste of Randolph and they usually have events going on from Christmas-themed cocktail months to stand up comedy nights and industry events.

The place is very hip, good music, good food and drinks. Nice place to have a date or a casual night out. Great service and good environment.
Cool atmosphere. No beer served here though. Just well drinks.
Consistently phenomenal service, drinks, and overall experience. Always my first choice for an after work happy hour, or when giving advice to friends in search of great cocktails.
Not a lot on the menu, drink-wise.  It was also a bit too small, I went on a Tuesday night and could barely get a seat.

They only have cocktails, no beer or wine.  The cocktail I tried was good, and the chili was very good.  Wait staff were pleasant.  They did inform us that after about 7pm one needs a reservation to get in.  Around 6pm it started getting pretty loud, to where normal conversation was not possible.
Great bar, amazing tasting. Highly recommend for locals and tourists.

The food is tasty, I guess if friends wanted to go there, I would, but it would never be my suggestion that we go there. 2 years later I'm back and I didn't eat, but the had a martini made with some special vodka. It was the best Martini I ever had. The staff there is awesome, it seems like I met everyone who worked there. I had a great time. I going to give it another star.
One of the best cocktail places I've been to . They can only serve their own liquor do even the bitters and what not are made in house.

A really good option to enjoy a few drinks with friends, service is exceptional, better that I have ever received in a bar in Chicago. There was no a bad shot or cocktail in this place for me. The Distillery behind the scenes is awesome and makes it even a more interesting experience. If you are looking for a nice place to have drinks you should definitely come around.

I love their unique cocktails where the spirits are distilled on premises. If you get a chance definitely do the distillery tour/tasting. It's really interesting to taste vodka in all it's different states before it's ready to be bottled. I only knocked off 1 star b/c this place can be realllly slow bringing out your cocktail. Make sure you have time to stay if you come in.
I had a spectacular burger and a tasty cocktail here
Great staff, with drinks and food to boot.
Good cocktails ! Great your guide!!

The food and drinks were great. But the service was so bad that it ruined our experience. The person who we assumed to be our server seemed so uninterested in serving us, but I guess that can be the affect of an automatic gratuity system. Not mad we went once, but probably won’t return.

Becoming a go to spot for us. Right off the train, has fantastic service, and great drinks. I have learned a lot more about liquors from the bartenders there, who also make some killer cocktails. Even when they are packed, and it can get a bit crowded, the service is still amazing. Great place to enjoy some great local spirits in a cool atmosphere with the distillery right behind the glass.

Amazing cocktails. Some of the best I've ever had. Trying all the unique spirits is always fun as well. The bartenders will also make a drink out a spirit of you specify what you like. They do have food which is simple but good.
What a place. Stylish, but comfy. Professional, but laid back. They were filing. Best drinks ever. Seriously.
Alex put the “enthusiasm” in “spirits enthusiast”. Very fun tour, great booze.

The cocktails here are very good. The mixologists are to notch, and the bar food is absolutely great. The staff is awesome, so willing to explain anything to you, and they make you feel they are genuinely happy to have you there. My favorite cocktail is  Rosemary's Baby. It's sweet, sour and savory. I have bought everything they make here, and I have bought them over and over. They are very good.
Great cocktails, somewhat pricey and hard to get a table

Fantastic cocktails, intimate environt but will get tight very quickly on busy nights. Apps are kinda a joke, two hardboiled eggs fit sux dollars our a coffee cup of mixed nuts.  When drinks are strong they might want to offer more...
Fun place to stop for an unusual beverage on your way to the restaurant row
Amazing
Delightful staff! Get the Frida! An intimate setting and easy night. We were very well taken care of. Will totally go again.
Awesome!!!

It was a nice place and sampling of spirits would have been nice. However there was four of us there and we all felt suckered after getting the bill for doing shots. Would have been cheaper to offer us bottles rather then drink shots for the time we were there. We had to beg for the waiter to get us anything and just felt ignored from the moment we walked in. For the price we paid we should have received much better service. Been there done it and will never go there again.
Love the unique cocktails here. The staff can be rude at times.
Brought my boyfriend for the 'Christmas Story' pop up. Had a great time! Awesome drinks and surprisingly good food.

Outstanding distilled products - their vodka is particularly good. The mixed drinks are quite good as well, showcasing their product well. The food available is all small plates, but we made a nice dinner out of it. Atmosphere is an upscale bar, so it's a bit loud.
Great cocktails.
A free taste of gin and juice makes for a great welcome to a quality distillery in downtown Chicago.

The service here was nice and they were quick to get us seated. However, the cocktails fell flat. I had a gin based drink and I couldn't tell if it was the actual gin that didn't have any floral notes to it or if the cocktail mixers was what brought it down - there was no depth to it. Best jerk wings in the city. Only sold during spring and summer months
Fun atmosphere and delicious vodka cocktails
Great atmosphere,  Great DJ
They cocktails and bartenders are the best.Love this place.

Very good cocktails from their own distilled spirits.  Food is limited to small plates of good quality ingredients or small sandwiches.  It can become loud when crowded. Bartenders are eager to talk about the spirits made there.
Drinks were great, but service was amazing. The bartender (unfortunately can’t remember his name) let us try a bunch of the spirits and even gave us a flight on the house!

Came here for a friends bday post dinner. They do have food, but it's more snacky options rather than dinner. I tried the baron takes tea and the cease and desist - the latter tastes like a red hot that has been melted. Maybe good for your throat? the baron takes tea was not tea tasting at all, and I really liked this drink, I think they had muddled some fennel in it, great taste over all.  This place is loud for sure, but they do distill and infuse their own gin and vodka. Good for a night out for drinks and they reserve tables/ areas for your party.  What's really cool is that they do tours of the distillery area for you to learn their process and point of differentiation, and do a tasting with that as well. Definitely worth checking out.
Excellent cocktails, great service, and an intimate atmosphere
Great place. Strong drinks 😋

Cocktails are amazing
One of the best places to have a drink in the city-true mixology

Excellent cocktails made with local ingredients. Passionate staff. Bites are good, too.
Brian is the best bartender I've ever had. He was engaging and helpful! Very creative drinks were served. Loved every minute of my visit here.

One of the best cocktail places in Chicago. Cease and Desist is the best and I cannot even remember how many of those drinks I've had so far. Was fortunate enough to get the recipe and I make it now when we throw House parties. They also used to make Gooey butter cake which was phenomenal but unfortunately is not available anymore on their menu.

Just drinks no food but worth a visit for the experience alone. Fantastic cocktails brilliant informative  staff and you can see into the distillery whilst you enjoy those freshly made drinks. Also loved the tasters.
Cool place. I wasn't that impressed with the spirits though
Pretty good drinks and friendly environment.
Awesome place! Great bar staff that make really good cocktails. The food is amazing.
Very unique place!
Was not an enjoyable experience. Waiter was inattentive, food was average, drinks were underwhelming for how much they were hyped up to be.
Greta cocktails always changing and a fun staff too!
The staff was amazing. They were knowledgeable. I dont drink vodka. They had a Moscow mule and I asked them to make it Kentucky and they knew exactly what I wanted. Will visit again when in Chicago.
Loved the tour. Craft drinks are amazing. Great vibe and delicious food.

I am a gin connoisseur- my motto "Gin is my Friend."This is one of the finest gins I've ever tasted. It's special when you really do not have to mix it. It's great with just ice. And I appreciate the opaque bottle. No one can tell how much I drank. :)
Assortment of premium craft whiskey.
Tasty cocktails and fast, friendly service. The Rasputin's Eye cocktail (vodka, rum, beet, hibiscus, lemongrass, serrano, fennel, and lemon) was particularly good.

The prettiest distillery I've ever been to. We did the tour which was extremely entertaining, informative, and affordable. The cocktails are reasonably priced as well, and they are delicious. The service all around was excellent. I haven't done the food yet, but will be back soon to give it a go.
Outstanding cocktails and service.  Get the nuts - ALL THE NUTS.
Good drinks, high prices

CH Distillery has a great cocktail bar. Their servers and bartenders are well versed with the menu. The space is a bit small but also offer outdoor seating. You can also get a tour of the distillery where they make their own vodka.
Amazing. The drinks are unique and exceptional, the staff is more than willing to assist, and the small plates are just right.
Staff was more than accommodating. Didn't get into the food but they let us sample almost all of the spirits. A unique experience!
Phenomenal. Haven't tried all the different spirits yet, but the cocktails, service, and few spirits I did try are great.
Loved that they gave us an "amuse booze" when we arrived...witty wordplay.
Great bar with creative cocktails. Good service, knowledgeable staff.

Drinks are good but pricey. 18% tip is added to all bills which is fine for food but not on drinks. All liquor drinks are $12 but with tio and tax are almost $16. This place distills all of it's own liquor so you pay a premium. The food experience was very poor and extremely expensive for tiny portions. The hush puppies were too dry and you only get 5 for $9; the tiny and poorly flavored mussels were also regrettable $17 why tip/tax for a snack; the poutine didn't taste like poutine.
Great atmosphere and good prices
Wonderful place for fun cocktails. Food is good but nothing special. Fun to sit at the bar, awesome bartenders.
Interesting venue, but rather small. Knowledgeable and friendly staff, distillery tours available.
Awesome atmosphere, you can see the distillery equipment from the bar through great big windows. Cocktails and food options are great.

Stopped in here while I was waiting for my table at Avec down the street. I got the old fashioned since I am an old school whiskey drinker. It was quite good and came at a fair price. The atmosphere and service was phenomenal. Our server was glad to explain all the drinks to us and help out with any questions we had. He was also genuinely interested in our feedback on the drinks and what we liked / didn't like.
Who doesn't love vodka! Must try the limoncello!
Only had drinks but hands down best mojito I've ever had!
Great cocktails. Specialize in vodka and gin. Bartenders mix both drinks and conversation well. They are very knowledgeable too and willing to share.

Wonderful place for drinks around the holiday! Came here during their "A Christmas Story" theme and was impressed by their unique and list of drinks. Would come again and recommend- great olace to pop in and sit down to have drinks!

Nice bar, good atmosphere! Love the gingerbread mule drink, my boyfriend had their old fashioned and like it. We also ordered a side of cheese and it came with toast and jelly! They don't have good food options so don't come here hungry.... Overall a great bar for hang out :)
Great drinks and cool place!
Tour is fun
Good cocktails made with their own spirits
Toured the distillery which was fantastic. Had a great tour guide. Food was good. Drinks were the best!
Had a chance to experience the tour but what really made the time great was the tremendous staff and management!  Treated me like family (only better) :)
Exceptional and creative cocktails. We did not like one out of three so they did not charge us for it.
Awesome cocktails over here.
Delicious drinks and food!!
Drink's are incredible
Excellent service. Delicious cocktails. Almost everything is made in house, with the exception of the bitters. Pricing is great for what you get and they let you sample endlessly.
Great bar!

Amazing hand crafted cocktails with an even more amazing attentive staff.  Executive Chef Pablo Madrigal puts out a spectacular menu of fresh appetizers and entrees to fit any palate.  Highly recommend a visit.
Great place to meet with friends. The drinks are fantastic.
there is good ! I like there!
Sat in the "distillery lounge", aka we ran out of room, so here's a spot in back by the tanks behind a curtain and put up a temporary bar.  Their spirits are awesome though!
Great signature drinks
Love their cream lemoncello!

A unique bar, restaurant, and distillery in the heart of Chicago. Very cool view into the distillery from the bar. Innovative cocktails using spirits made on-site. Friendly staff and knowledgeable bartenders complete the experience!
So cool to see all the brewing taking place epic
Spicy Persuasion and Happy Endings the best drinks of the house

Creative cocktails; especially loved the spicy and intriguing Doctors Orders. Had the whiskey duck tacos which were delicious, just wish they were bigger, lol. Fine dining for you. Perfect for a romantic night out. Service was excellent.
You get a little sample of a specialty drink just for sitting down during happy hour.  The cocktails are awesome and I love the way the menu is organized.  Highly recommend to anyone.
Adds 18% to your ticket automatically as a "service charge" in lieu of a tip. Too bad, if the service is good, I usually give 25-30%. Won't be back.

A fantastic addition to the growing Chicago restaurant and bar scene. Handcrafted drinks made using the distillery's finest products.  Highly recommend for a fantastic cocktail and night out. The food menu was designed specifically to pair with the drinks.
Great for cocktails!
Inventive and fun cocktails that rotate every few months. Friendly and enthusiastic staff, very cool vibe. A West Loop staple.

Fantastic rotational cocktails. Delicious rotational menu. Absolute must are the mussels and artisan meats and cheese. And whichever cocktail peaks your intrest. My favorite of the night is sexy tiki goodness. Adam and Pablo are fantastiic and everyone servicing is super cool.

I enjoy every this place every time I visit. My go-to drink would definitely be the Cease and Desist. Appetizers her come at a pretty penny but are worth the price.  This is a great place to go to if you want something different from your everyday bar.
Decor is xlnt, however $10 for a tiny cocktail was not. Limited food menus if you don't eat goat.

A beautiful modern space with some wicked delish drinks. I am not usually a fan of vodka and I told this to the bartender during my first visit. His response was to give me a taste of their ice cold vodka straight up. *shiver*. But, I am who I am- and that means I've got to try anything that is put in front of me so I puffed out my chest and braved the cold (vodka, that is)! And you know what? It was DELICIOUS. So smooth and easy to drink, even on it's own. Their cocktail list is studded with perfectly executed classic beverages along with many tea infused or peppercorn speckled options if you are looking for an interesting twist. Their cocktails and spirits are a must, however, I would not shy you away from checking out their food items either. Prepared in a cube like open air area right next to the bar, irresistible scents will be wafting your way as you enjoy your ice cold hand crafted beverages. Cheers!

I went to CH Distillery for afterwork drinks and dinner with the girls. They were featuring a special menu from Union Sushi. I ordered the spicy shrimp rolls and tuna cup which was delish. I like the vibe of the place. Great scenery and people. My friend ordered a drink that she didn't like and the server happily exchanged it for another. I'll definitely be back.

From the moment you walk in the sleek space, gleaming distillery equipment and minimalist style tell you that this is no ordinary bar. They make gin, vodka, whiskey and a few other spirits on site and use only local ingredients in both the distilling process and their cocktails. I'm a huge cocktail nerd and throughly enjoyed the Cease and Desist and a seasonal drink with hints of Earl Grey tea.

Trendy spot for drinks and apps, but not really somewhere to go if you're looking for a full meal.  There are a variety of options, and the onsite distillery is cool, but the tiny menu portions add up quickly.

This place is cool! The environment is upscale & modern. I was here with a large group of people and they were easily able to accommodate us all and the service was excellent.  We all had a couple different cocktails. You have to try their Limoncello and all of their custom made cocktails.

If you like sweet drinks then I would suggest the Orient express. Sweet, creamy, and smooth with a very nice presentation. If you like something bitter then go for the cease and desist. You can't go wrong with either one. Other recommendations are the daiquiri and the potato pancakes. The price seems right for the quality drinks you get.

So yes it's kind of pricey. I wouldn't go here and order any of the snacks as their portion size seems to be more of a tasting than anything, but the food quality is good so I will give them a pass. We had for drinks while we were there.  Gin and tonic, was quite tasty but not what I expected. The gin they use has a smoky quality that is pleasant, but I don't understand why they don't use their London dry gin in the drink and stay true to the classic cocktail. I can't complain too much because the drink was great though.  The daiquiri was exceptional and would have Hemingway himself coming back for more.  The cease and desist, was my absolute favorite drink and makes for an excellent reason to stop by this place on your way home from a dinner on Randolph street.  The Orient express was also tasty and had a great presentation.
Limited set of drinks - mostly their own gin and vodka, but if that is what you like, this is a good place to check out.
Excellent spirits, fresh and interesting atmosphere, and friendly and helpful staff. The signature cocktails and food menu were top quality as well.
